"[\"Infinity Energy, INC.\", \"Use of Company Property Policy\", \"Purpose\\n\", \"The purpose of this policy is to ensure that all property maintained by Infinity Energy, INC. is kept in the best possible working condition and to ensure proper use of such property and Infinity Energy, INC. networks.\\n\", \"\\u201cProperty,\\u201d as the term is used in this policy, is defined as any piece of equipment, furnishing, vehicle, building or supply leased, owned, donated or otherwise in the custodial care of Infinity Energy, INC. or any person acting as its agent.\", \"No Infinity Energy, INC. employee should expect any privacy on Infinity Energy, INC. premises or when using Infinity Energy, INC. property or networks, except that which is required by law.\", \"General Guidelines on the Use of Company Property\", \"All Infinity Energy, INC. employees must maintain his or her work environment in an orderly fashion and follow all Infinity Energy, INC. rules to ensure its proper use and maintenance.\", \"Any employee who is found to have neglected or misused Infinity Energy, INC. property will be subject to disciplinary action up to and including termination. If an employee\\u2019s misuse of Infinity Energy, INC. property damages the property, Infinity Energy, INC. reserves the right to require the employee to pay all or part of the cost to repair or replace the property. Misappropriation of Infinity Energy, INC. property is grounds for immediate termination and possible criminal action.\", \" Infinity Energy, INC. property (including computers, pagers, telephones, cellphones, copiers, fax machines, Internet services and printers) is intended for business use only. Limited personal use as necessary is allowable but should be the exception and not the rule. Infinity Energy, INC. reserves the right to discipline employees for excessive personal use of company property. \\n\", \"Use of Company Vehicles\", \"Any employee for whom driving is an essential job duty must be authorized and approved by the Fleet Department to drive Infinity Energy, INC. vehicles. It is the responsibility of the employee driver of a Infinity Energy, INC. vehicle to ensure that the vehicle is in full operational condition before each use. The employee driver will sign a vehicle log report noting any problems with, or damage to, the vehicle before each use. Should the employee return the vehicle to the company with damage to the vehicle, the vehicle log report will be used as support evidence of the condition of the vehicle before it was used by the employee driver. Any vehicle found to be unsafe will be removed from the operational fleet until appropriate maintenance or repairs have occurred.\", \"Use and Dissemination of Company Information\", \"\\u201cInformation,\\u201d as the term is used in this policy, includes without limitation any information owned or used by Infinity Energy, INC., such as:\", \"Any company employee, customer or client lists.\", \"Any company database information, including addresses and telephone numbers.\", \"Any information from Infinity Energy, INC. employee personnel files, including employee addresses, telephone numbers, employment status and wage history.\", \"Any photographs, videotapes and sound clips of any Infinity Energy, INC. employee, customer or client.\", \"Only those employees who are authorized by Infinity Energy, INC.\\u2019s board of directors or executive team, or whose job description permits them to do so, may speak on behalf of Infinity Energy, INC. Notwithstanding the foregoing, specific permission from the Infinity Energy, INC.\\u2019s board of directors or executive team will be required before any Infinity Energy, INC. employee may disseminate confidential Infinity Energy, INC. information.\", \"No employee may knowingly dispense such information to any outside party unless authorization has been granted. This could include other employees who do not have the right to know such information. Any breach will be considered a violation of Infinity Energy, INC. policy concerning confidentiality, and it may constitute a violation of state or federal law.\", \"Monitoring of Network Communications\", \"Infinity Energy, INC. reserves the right to monitor at any time any communications that use Infinity Energy, INC. networks in any way, including data, voice mail, telephone logs, Internet use and network traffic, to determine proper use. \", \"Infinity Energy, INC. will review network communications activity and will analyze use patterns. Infinity Energy, INC. may choose to publish these data to ensure that company resources in these areas are being used according to this policy. \", \"No employee may knowingly disable any network software or system identified as a monitoring tool.\", \"\"]"